# Purchase Path Extension Sample

Sample project to demonstrate Button In-App Checkout customization via [Purchase Path Extensions](https://developer.usebutton.com/guides/publishers/ios/checkout-extensions).

## Getting started

### 1. Add your Button app id in `AppDelegate.m` or `AppDelegate.swift`.

**AppDelegate.swift**
```swift
Button.shared().configure(withApplicationId: "__APP_ID_HERE__", completion: nil)
```

### 2. Update Purchase Path urls [Optional]

Purchase Path urls should be configured to match your organization's approved partnerships.

**MainController.swift**
```swift
private var yourExampleMerchantUrl = URL(string: "http://jet.com")!
```

## Purchase Path Extensions

[Purchase Path Extensions](https://developer.usebutton.com/guides/publishers/ios/checkout-extensions) can be used to customize the In-App Checkout experience.

You can customize the experience by modifying the `SampleExtension` class.

**SampleExtension.swift**
```swift
class SampleExtension: NSObject, PurchasePathExtension {

    func checkoutDidInitialize(_ checkout: BrowserInterface) {
        checkout.setTitle("Jet")
        checkout.setTitleColor(.purple)
        checkout.setSubtitle("www.jet.com")
        checkout.setSubtitleColor(.purple)
        checkout.setTopBarBackgroundColor(.white)
        checkout.setTopBarTintColor(.purple)
    }

    func checkout(_ checkout: BrowserInterface, didNavigateTo url: URL) {
        if url.absoluteString.contains("shoes") {
            checkout.setSubtitle("2% Cash Back")
        }
        else {
            checkout.setSubtitle("")
        }
    }

    func checkoutDidClose() {
        
    }
}
```

